data.enText: the general arrangement, plan, design, etc. of sth

data.chText: 新的智力竞赛节目的总体安排结果证明很受欢迎。
data.enText: The format of the new quiz show has proved popular.
the shape and size of a book, magazine, etc.

data.chText: 他们用新的版式出版这杂志。
data.enText: They've brought out the magazine in a new format.
the way in which data is stored or held to be worked on by a computer
to prepare a computer disk so that data can be recorded on it
to arrange text in a particular way on a page or a screen

tr: the general appearance of a publication
the organization of information according to preset specifications (usually for computer processing)
divide (a disk) into marked sectors so that it may store data
example: Please format this disk before entering data!

tr: determine the arrangement of (data) for storage and display (in computer science)
set (printed matter) into a specific format
example: Format this letter so it can be printed out

value.def: The format of something is the way or order in which it is arranged and presented.

example.ex: I had met with him to explain the format of the programme and what we had in mind.
example.tran: 我已经和他当面解释了我们节目的形式以及我们的想法。

value.def: The format of a piece of computer software or a musical recording is the type of equipment on which it is designed to be used or played. For example, possible formats for a musical recording are CD and cassette.

example.ex: His latest album is available on all formats.
example.tran: 他的最新专辑有各种载体形式。

value.tran: (电脑软件或音乐的)载体形式

value.def: To format a computer disk means to run a program so that the disk can be written on.
To format a piece of computer text or graphics means to arrange the way in which it appears when it is printed or is displayed on a screen.

example.ex: When text is saved from a Web page, it is often very badly formatted with many short lines.
example.tran: 从网页上转存文本时，往往会出现许多短行，格式也乱了。

value.tran: 编排(计算机文本或图表)的格式
